items.name: Raised Leg Invitation
items.description:
Pose in which the subject lays on their side raising one leg alluringly presenting their crotch. Although this was not trained to be explicitly nude by necessity, given the subject matter and training data be aware that images may tend towards nudity and will almost definitely be considered NSFW by most standards.

The model definitely struggles with anatomy and perspective foreshortening sometimes, especially depending on other contributing LoRAs. Expect some creatures on your way. Hand and often feet are also in frame, which only adds to the anatomical artifacting.

Lowering the weight of the pose slightly (e.g. down to 0.8) may improve results.

items.name: END
items.description:
厌倦了,这东西有无限的组合方式,这个tag下画面好点,那个tag出来的效果又特烂,与其再在这精神内耗不如去干点别的有意思的事情了,在评鉴了几万张ai图后看着崩坏的手指混乱的细节,再去欣赏人类艺术家的作品,得出一个感悟不是你的终究不是你的,即使再怎么惊艳,这几个月通过学习ai也获得了不少,也让我觉得比起去思考ai会不会杀死行业焦虑,不如去多加提升自己,任何东西终究只是工具,最终还是以人为本,也许以后又有大进步还会回来也许不会,玩的开心

Tired of it, this thing has infinite combinations. The image under this tag is better, and the effect produced by that tag is particularly bad. Instead of being consumed by this mental state, it's better to do something else interesting. After reviewing tens of thousands of AI images, I look at the chaotic details of the broken fingers, and then appreciate the works of human artists. I come to the realization that what is not yours is not yours, even if it's amazing, I have gained a lot through studying AI in the past few months, It also makes me feel that instead of thinking about whether AI will kill industry anxiety, it's better to improve oneself more. Everything is ultimately just a tool, and ultimately, it's still people-oriented. Perhaps there will be significant progress in the future, and perhaps not. Have a good time

items.name: Futura Alex Grey
items.description:
My rating vs expectation: 85%

(Read "about this version" for changes. The separation of the eyes bothers me. Will retrain in near future.)

All TIs I make depict real adults. Please apply it with good judgement. If you're the model and want this removed reach out to me via link below. I welcome all criticisms and suggestions with curiosity. If you like my work, buy me a house:
https://ko-fi.com/futurafree

This TI was trained in sd1.5 base with 5 vectors, 62 images, 20600 steps, and 332 epochs. This was finetuned for epiCRealism evo3 and Realistic Vision V4.0, but may work on others.

TIPS:

  • MUST be the first word in the prompt for likeness and consistency.

    • Example: futuraalex20600v52, portrait of a woman, long dress etc.

    • Not: Portrait of futuraalex20600v52, etc.

  • Recommended strength:

    • (0.98-1.0)

  • May produce red and purple artifacts with DPM++ 2M Karras at LOW sampling steps.

    • Fix: raise sampling steps above 25 always.

  • I use adetailer for all images, with mediapipe_face_full, blank pos and neg, 1024x1024, inpaint mask blur: 20, inpaint noise strength: 0.45.

  • Again, prompt in adetailer is left blank most of the time; (*exception*: if Loras/Lycoris is used and has significant impact on the appearance of the model's face, copy paste pos prompt without Loras/Lycoris into adetailer).

  • Upscaler I use: 4x_NMKD-Siax_200k.

items.name: Meg Ryan (JG)
items.description:
A commission of @Zorglub.

Meg Ryan is an American actress who became one of the most famous stars in Hollywood during the late 80s and 90s. She starred in some well-known movies (most of them romantic comedies) like When Harry Met Sally, Sleepless in Seattle, French Kiss, You've Got Mail or City of Angels.

140-step TI trained on a dataset of 15 images with these settings.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

Building a good prompt with my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of (m3gry4n:0.99), a woman as a movie star, modelshoot style, (extremely detailed CG unity 8k wallpaper), photo of the most beautiful artwork in the world, professional majestic oil painting by Ed Blinkey, Atey Ghailan, Studio Ghibli, by Jeremy Mann, Greg Manchess, Antonio Moro, trending on ArtStation, trending on CGSociety, Intricate, High Detail, Sharp focus, dramatic, photorealistic painting art by midjourney and greg rutkowski, (white turtleneck top:1.2), ((movie premiere)), (long skirt), ((standing near a movie theater)), ((paparazzi in the background)), (looking at viewer:1.2), (detailed pupils:1.3), ((closeup portrait:1.1))"

items.name: Maverick
items.description:
💚 for Updates - I would love to see your reviews and images of this model, feel free to post them below!

I decided to take Aniwave 1 and merge in an idea of a series of semi-realistic style models along with various LoRa. I expected a scuffed result - though found the initial result to be fairly interesting and creative. *However, teeth at times may in fact be a bit scuffed.

I am not too big on semi-realistic styles in general. At a point I was aiming for this model have somewhat of an animated undertone/styling. Currently this model excels at a clean creative semi-animated/realistic approach. This model can range from photorealistic styles to semi-realistic to cartoon/animated in a very creative way.

Any updates to this one may try to refine those slight animated aspects a bit more while maintaining the clean semi-realistic detailing and hyper creative styling that currently exists. Also to perhaps weed out any awkward features and detail inaccuracies if possible.

I see a lot of flexibility with this one and haven't done as much testing with this one as others personally. I would love to hear how you find this model, feel free to let me know with images, comments, or reviews!

Recommended Use

There is a lot of variation in parameters for what works. Be aware on the styling you're choosing and use what you find best. The example images, gallery sections, and the quick start below are good starting points.

~20 steps, 7 scale, ~0.3-0.5 denoising, clip skip 1 or 2
